blindelof@sacbee.com 
A man was killed near the bike trail and Jibboom Street Monday night, according to Sacramento police. 
Sacramento police dispatchers received information about 8:30 p.m. Monday that an unconscious man had been found near the 400 block of Jibboom Street, just upriver from the I Street Bridge. 
Sacramento Fire Department firefighters were the first on the scene, followed by police officers. Fire department medical personnel declared the 34-year-old man dead. 
Homicide and Crime Scene Investigators were called to the scene to collect evidence and search for witnesses to the killing. Detectives said that the man was in a physical altercation with someone. 
The dead man, who has not yet been identified, suffered injury to his upper body. The suspect fled before the arrival of officers. 
No motive has been determined and no arrests have been made.
